<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="10" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="11.[192,1441,221,885]" pageId="11" pageNumber="10">
<bibRefCitation author="Aurivillius, C." box="[232,447,221,245]" pageId="11" pageNumber="10" pagination="361 - 403" refId="ref9261" refString="Aurivillius, C. 1920. Neue oder wenig bekannte Coleoptera Longicornia. 17. Arkiv for Zoologi 13 (9): 361 - 403." type="journal article" year="1920">Aurivillius (1920)</bibRefCitation>
described 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Aurivillius" authorityYear="1920" box="[578,861,221,245]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Amphicnaeia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cordigera">
<emphasis box="[578,861,221,245]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="10">Amphicnaeia cordigera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[877,962,221,245]" captionStart="Figures 29–32" captionStartId="19.[193,287,1848,1870]" captionTargetId="figure@19.[264,1368,495,1639]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="Figures 29–32. Rosalba cordigera. 29) Syntype of Amphicnaeia cordigera, dorsal habitus. 30–31) Rosalba rufescens, from Santos-Silva et al. (2018). 30) Dorsal habitus. 31) Lateral habitus. 32) Rosalba rufescens, holotype, from Santos-Silva et al. (2018)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3685683" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3685683/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="10">Fig. 29</figureCitation>
) from 
<collectingCountry box="[1042,1117,221,245]" name="Brazil" pageId="11" pageNumber="10">Brazil</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingRegion box="[1132,1312,221,245]" country="Brazil" name="Rio de Janeiro" pageId="11" pageNumber="10">Rio de Janeiro</collectingRegion>
), based on multiple specimens (exact number not specified). Although Aurivillius described the general pubescence of the elytra, he did not mention the presence or absence of erect setae. 
<bibRefCitation author="Breuning, S." box="[1098,1300,285,309]" pageId="11" pageNumber="10" pagination="109 - 182" refId="ref9600" refString="Breuning, S. 1960. Catalogue des Lamiaires du Monde (Col., Cerambycidae). Museum G. Frey, Tutzing bei Munchen 3: 109 - 182." type="journal article" year="1960">Breuning (1960)</bibRefCitation>
considered 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Aurivillius" authorityYear="1920" box="[192,340,317,341]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Amphicnaeia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cordigera">
<emphasis box="[192,340,317,341]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="10">A. cordigera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a form of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bates" authorityYear="1866" box="[498,616,317,341]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Amphicnaeia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lineata">
<emphasis box="[498,616,317,341]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="10">A. lineata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but subsequently 
<bibRefCitation author="Galileo, M. H. M. &amp; U. R. Martins" box="[849,1138,317,341]" pageId="11" pageNumber="10" pagination="37 - 41" refId="ref9738" refString="Galileo, M. H. M., and U. R. Martins. 2001. Notas sobre Amphicnaeia Bates, 1866 (Coleoptera, Cerambycidae, Lamiinae) com revalidacoes e descricoes de especies novas. Revista Brasileira de Entomologia 45 (1): 37 - 41." type="journal article" year="2001">Galileo &amp; Martins 2001</bibRefCitation>
revalidated the species.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[192,1441,221,885]" pageId="11" pageNumber="10">
<bibRefCitation author="Breuning, S." box="[232,450,349,373]" pageId="11" pageNumber="10" pagination="115 - 214" refId="ref9532" refString="Breuning, S. 1940 b. Novae species cerambycidarum. IX. Folia Zoologica et Hydrobiologica 10: 115 - 214." type="journal article" year="1940">Breuning (1940b)</bibRefCitation>
described 
<taxonomicName authority="Bates, 1866" authorityName="Breuning" authorityYear="1940" box="[589,818,349,373]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Aletretia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rufescens">
<emphasis box="[589,818,349,373]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="10">Aletretia rufescens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, based on a single specimen from 
<collectingCountry box="[1264,1339,349,373]" name="Brazil" pageId="11" pageNumber="10">Brazil</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingRegion country="Brazil" name="Rio de Janeiro" pageId="11" pageNumber="10">Rio de Janeiro</collectingRegion>
). Later, 
<bibRefCitation author="Breuning, S." box="[389,587,381,405]" pageId="11" pageNumber="10" pagination="109 - 182" refId="ref9600" refString="Breuning, S. 1960. Catalogue des Lamiaires du Monde (Col., Cerambycidae). Museum G. Frey, Tutzing bei Munchen 3: 109 - 182." type="journal article" year="1960">Breuning (1960)</bibRefCitation>
transferred the species to 
<taxonomicName authority="Thomson, 1864" authorityName="Thomson" authorityYear="1864" box="[909,1203,381,405]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Rosalba" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[909,1008,381,405]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="10">Rosalba</emphasis>
Thomson, 1864
</taxonomicName>
. After this, the species was mentioned only in catalogues and checklists, until Santos-Silva et al. (2018), who redescribed, provided new state records, and illustrated the species. According to them: “ 
<bibRefCitation author="Breuning, S." box="[1129,1328,445,469]" pageId="11" pageNumber="10" pagination="209 - 335" refId="ref9632" refString="Breuning, S. 1971. Revision des especes americaines de la tribue des Apomecynini Lac. (Coleoptera, Cerambycidae). Entomologische Abhandlungen aus dem Staatliches Museum fur Tierkunde 37 (3): 209 - 335." type="journal article" year="1971">Breuning (1971)</bibRefCitation>
reported (translated): “Perhaps this is just a poorly preserved specimen of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Melzer" baseAuthorityYear="1934" box="[982,1071,477,501]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Rosalba" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="malleri">
<emphasis box="[982,1071,477,501]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="10">malleri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
MELZ.” Actually, the description (Breuning 1940[b]) and redescription (
<bibRefCitation author="Breuning, S." box="[726,910,509,533]" pageId="11" pageNumber="10" pagination="209 - 335" refId="ref9632" refString="Breuning, S. 1971. Revision des especes americaines de la tribue des Apomecynini Lac. (Coleoptera, Cerambycidae). Entomologische Abhandlungen aus dem Staatliches Museum fur Tierkunde 37 (3): 209 - 335." type="journal article" year="1971">Breuning 1971</bibRefCitation>
) of 
<taxonomicName authority="Bates, 1866" authorityName="Breuning" authorityYear="1940" box="[960,1108,509,533]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Aletretia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rufescens">
<emphasis box="[960,1108,509,533]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="10">R. rufescens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
do not allow us to be sure about the differences regarding to 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Melzer" baseAuthorityYear="1934" box="[606,728,541,565]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Rosalba" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="malleri">
<emphasis box="[606,728,541,565]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="10">R. malleri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. However, from what it is possible to see, the 
<typeStatus box="[1275,1379,541,565]" pageId="11" pageNumber="10">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName authority="Bates, 1866" authorityName="Breuning" authorityYear="1940" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Aletretia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rufescens">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="10">R. rufescens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has the elytral apex less narrowed toward apex than in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Melzer" baseAuthorityYear="1934" box="[979,1101,573,597]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Rosalba" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="malleri">
<emphasis box="[979,1101,573,597]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="10">R. malleri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Furthermore, examination of the pubescence that remained on the elytron of the 
<typeStatus box="[845,949,605,629]" pageId="11" pageNumber="10">holotype</typeStatus>
(
<figureCitation box="[964,1049,605,629]" captionStart="Figures 29–32" captionStartId="19.[193,287,1848,1870]" captionTargetId="figure@19.[264,1368,495,1639]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="Figures 29–32. Rosalba cordigera. 29) Syntype of Amphicnaeia cordigera, dorsal habitus. 30–31) Rosalba rufescens, from Santos-Silva et al. (2018). 30) Dorsal habitus. 31) Lateral habitus. 32) Rosalba rufescens, holotype, from Santos-Silva et al. (2018)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3685683" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3685683/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="10">Fig. 32</figureCitation>
) suggests that the arrangement is most similar to the specimens studied by us (
<figureCitation box="[772,904,637,661]" captionStart="Figures 29–32" captionStartId="19.[193,287,1848,1870]" captionTargetId="figure@19.[264,1368,495,1639]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="Figures 29–32. Rosalba cordigera. 29) Syntype of Amphicnaeia cordigera, dorsal habitus. 30–31) Rosalba rufescens, from Santos-Silva et al. (2018). 30) Dorsal habitus. 31) Lateral habitus. 32) Rosalba rufescens, holotype, from Santos-Silva et al. (2018)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3685683" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3685683/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="10">Fig. 30–31</figureCitation>
), rather than to 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Melzer" baseAuthorityYear="1934" box="[1105,1228,637,661]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Rosalba" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="malleri">
<emphasis box="[1105,1228,637,661]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="10">R. malleri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.”
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[192,1441,221,885]" pageId="11" pageNumber="10">
Validation that the 
<taxonomicName authority="sensu Santos-Silva et al. (2018)" authorityName="Santos-Silva" authorityYear="2018" box="[471,1001,669,693]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Aletretia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rufescens">
<emphasis box="[471,691,669,693]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="10">R. rufescens sensu</emphasis>
Santos-Silva et al. (2018)
</taxonomicName>
corresponds to the true 
<taxonomicName authority="Bates, 1866" authorityName="Bates" authorityYear="1866" box="[1295,1440,669,693]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Aletretia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rufescens">
<emphasis box="[1295,1440,669,693]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="10">R. rufescens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
then it is certain this species is a junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Aurivillius" authorityYear="1920" box="[839,1124,701,725]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Amphicnaeia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cordigera">
<emphasis box="[839,1124,701,725]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="10">Amphicnaeia cordigera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and belongs in the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thomson" authorityYear="1864" box="[192,291,733,757]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Rosalba" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[192,291,733,757]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="10">Rosalba</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(the main difference between 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thomson" authorityYear="1864" box="[665,764,733,757]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Rosalba" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[665,764,733,757]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="10">Rosalba</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bates" authorityYear="1866" box="[825,987,733,757]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Amphicnaeia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[825,987,733,757]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="10">Amphicnaeia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is the absence (
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thomson" authorityYear="1864" box="[1184,1283,733,757]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Rosalba" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1184,1283,733,757]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="10">Rosalba</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) or presence (
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bates" authorityYear="1866" box="[201,363,765,789]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Amphicnaeia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[201,363,765,789]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="10">Amphicnaeia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) of erect setae on elytra).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[192,1441,221,885]" pageId="11" pageNumber="10">
It is not possible to be sure about 
<emphasis box="[651,1137,797,821]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="10">
<taxonomicName box="[651,1012,797,821]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Amphicnaeia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="cordigera" subSpecies="sensu">Amphicnaeia cordigera sensu</taxonomicName>
auctorum
</emphasis>
, without examination of the specimens studied by them. Accordingly, no changes can be made simply based on the literature pertaining to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Aurivillius" authorityYear="1920" box="[359,507,861,885]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Amphicnaeia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cordigera">
<emphasis box="[359,507,861,885]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="10">A. cordigera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
